House Resolution 952
By: Representatives Willis of the 55th and Crawford of the 89th
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Risks Associated with Hair Straightening Products;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, a recent study by the University of Texas' MD Anderson Cancer Center found
4 a link between chemicals in hair straightening products and breast cancer, demonstrating a
5 60 percent increase in risk for some women who use them; and
6 WHEREAS, some hair straightening treatments, such as relaxers, contain chemicals known
7 as endocrine disputers that can interfere with human hormones; and
8 WHEREAS, a 2019 study by the International Journal of Cancer found that for women who
9 used hair straightening or relaxing products regularly, the risk of breast cancer increased by
10 31 percent; and
11 WHEREAS, additional determinations are needed concerning the health risks associated with
12 using hair straightening products and whether consumer warnings are warranted; and
